    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-07-18T04:00:04+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-18T04:00:04+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-17T18:30:04Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-17T18:30:04Z">
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A strong high pressure system over Victoria will continue to extend a ridge over South Australia. A weak trough develops in the west on Tuesday.</text>
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-07-18T05:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-19T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-17T19:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-18T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Dry. Areas of morning fog, mainly on and east of the ranges. Cold start with morning frost patches through the southeast. Maximum temperatures slightly above average. East to northeasterly winds.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-07-19T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-20T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-18T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-19T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Dry. The chance of morning fog on and east of the ranges. The chance of frost about parts of the northern agricultural area and south of the North East Pastoral district. Maximum temperatures slightly above average. North to northeasterly winds.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-07-20T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-21T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-19T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-20T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Dry. Maximum temperatures slightly above average. Northeast to northwesterly winds.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-07-21T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-22T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-20T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-21T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">
                    <p>Dry, apart from a possible late light shower about western Kangaroo Island. Maximum temperatures slightly above average. North to northwesterly winds, shifting southwest to southerly about the southwest later.</p>
                    <p/>
                    <p>Cumulative rainfall totals to the end of Tuesday: Mostly dry.</p>
                </text>
            </forecast-period>
